## Phase 3: Remove `ogImage`

### Overview

Delete `ogImage` from all schemas, the `ContentSeoData` type, and all 17 MDX frontmatter files. Add `featuredImage` to MDX files that should have a hero image.

### Changes Required

#### 1. Remove `ogImage` from `BasePageSchema`

**File**: `apps/www/src/lib/content-schemas.ts`

```ts
// Before (lines 14-24):
const BasePageSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1),
  description: z.string().min(50).max(160),
  keywords: z.array(z.string().min(1)).min(3).max(20),
  canonicalUrl: z.url(),
  ogTitle: z.string().min(1).max(70),
  ogDescription: z.string().min(50).max(160),
  ogImage: z.url(),
  noindex: z.boolean().default(false),
  nofollow: z.boolean().default(false),
});

// After:
const BasePageSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1),
  description: z.string().min(50).max(160),
  keywords: z.array(z.string().min(1)).min(3).max(20),
  canonicalUrl: z.url(),
  ogTitle: z.string().min(1).max(70),
  ogDescription: z.string().min(50).max(160),
  noindex: z.boolean().default(false),
  nofollow: z.boolean().default(false),
});
```

#### 2. Remove `ogImage` from `ContentSeoData`

**File**: `apps/www/src/lib/content-schemas.ts`

```ts
// Before (lines 91-104):
