## Pattern Examples: `opengraph-image.tsx` Route Handlers

### Pattern 1: Static Home Image (No params, no `generateStaticParams`)
**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/www/src/app/(app)/(marketing)/(landing)/opengraph-image.tsx`

```tsx
import { HomeLayout } from "@repo/og";
import { OG_HEIGHT, OG_WIDTH } from "@repo/og/brand";
import { ImageResponse } from "next/og";
import { loadOGFonts } from "~/lib/og-fonts";

export const runtime = "nodejs";
export const alt = "Lightfast – The Operating Layer for Agents and Apps";
export const size = { width: OG_WIDTH, height: OG_HEIGHT };
export const contentType = "image/png";

export default async function Image() {
  const fonts = await loadOGFonts();
  return new ImageResponse(<HomeLayout />, { ...size, fonts });
}
```

### Pattern 2: Slug-parameterized Content Image (with source lookup and not-found guard)
**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/www/src/app/(app)/(marketing)/(content)/blog/[slug]/opengraph-image.tsx`

```tsx
import { ContentLayout } from "@repo/og";
import { OG_HEIGHT, OG_WIDTH } from "@repo/og/brand";
import { ImageResponse } from "next/og";
import { getBlogPage } from "~/app/(app)/(content)/_lib/source";
import { loadOGFonts } from "~/lib/og-fonts";

export const runtime = "nodejs";
export const alt = "Lightfast Blog Post";
export const size = { width: OG_WIDTH, height: OG_HEIGHT };
export const contentType = "image/png";

export default async function Image({
  params,
}: {
  params: Promise<{ slug: string }>;
}) {
  const { slug } = await params;
  const page = getBlogPage([slug]);
  const fonts = await loadOGFonts();

  if (!page) {
    return new ImageResponse(<div>Not Found</div>, { ...size });
  }

  const { title, description, category, publishedAt, authors } = page.data;

  return new ImageResponse(
    <ContentLayout
      author={authors[0]?.name ?? "Lightfast"}
      category={category.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + category.slice(1)}
      date={new Date(publishedAt).toLocaleDateString("en-US", {
        year: "numeric",
        month: "long",
        day: "numeric",
      })}
      description={description}
      title={title}
    />,
    { ...size, fonts }
  );
}
```

### Pattern 3: Changelog Slug Image (same structure, fewer props passed to layout)
**Found in**: `/Users/jeevanpillay/Code/@lightfastai/lightfast/apps/www/src/app/(app)/(marketing)/(content)/changelog/[slug]/opengraph-image.tsx`

Same shape as Pattern 2 but imports `getChangelogPage`, uses no `author`, passes a hardcoded `category="Changelog"`.

**Key aspects common to all three**:
- `export const runtime = "nodejs"` — always present
- `export const alt`, `export const size`, `export const contentType` — always the four named exports
