## Implementation Approach

Three phases, each independently deployable:
1. **Additive** — new schema field + new OG handlers (zero behavioral change)
2. **Swap** — migrate all consumers from `ogImage` to `featuredImage` / programmatic OG
3. **Cleanup** — remove `ogImage` from schemas, types, and frontmatter

---

## Phase 1: Add `featuredImage` + OG Route Handlers

### Overview

Add the `featuredImage` optional field to `ContentPageSchema` and create `opengraph-image.tsx` handlers for the three content types that lack them (legal, docs, API reference). No existing behavior changes.

### Changes Required

#### 1. Schema: Add `featuredImage` to `ContentPageSchema`

**File**: `apps/www/src/lib/content-schemas.ts`

Add `featuredImage` to `ContentPageSchema` (after line 31):

```ts
const ContentPageSchema = BasePageSchema.extend({
  authors: z.array(AuthorSchema).min(1),
  publishedAt: z.iso.datetime(),
  updatedAt: z.iso.datetime(),
  faq: z.array(FaqItemSchema).min(1),
  featuredImage: z.string().startsWith("/images/").optional(),
});
```

No changes to `BlogPostSchema`, `ChangelogEntrySchema`, `LegalPageSchema`, or `DocsPageSchema` — they inherit from `ContentPageSchema` or `BasePageSchema` as appropriate. Only blog and changelog (which extend `ContentPageSchema`) get the field.

#### 2. Legal OG Handler

**File** (new): `apps/www/src/app/(app)/(marketing)/legal/[slug]/opengraph-image.tsx`

```tsx
import { ContentLayout } from "@repo/og";
import { OG_HEIGHT, OG_WIDTH } from "@repo/og/brand";
import { ImageResponse } from "next/og";
import { getLegalPage } from "~/app/(app)/(content)/_lib/source";
import { loadOGFonts } from "~/lib/og-fonts";

export const runtime = "nodejs";
export const alt = "Lightfast Legal";
export const size = { width: OG_WIDTH, height: OG_HEIGHT };
export const contentType = "image/png";

export default async function Image({
  params,
}: {
  params: Promise<{ slug: string }>;
}) {
  const { slug } = await params;
  const page = getLegalPage([slug]);
  const fonts = await loadOGFonts();

  if (!page) {
    return new ImageResponse(<div>Not Found</div>, { ...size });
  }

  const { title, description, updatedAt } = page.data;

  return new ImageResponse(
    <ContentLayout
      category="Legal"
      date={new Date(updatedAt).toLocaleDateString("en-US", {
        year: "numeric",
        month: "long",
        day: "numeric",
      })}
      description={description}
      title={title}
    />,
    { ...size, fonts }
  );
}
```

Also add `generateStaticParams` for static generation:

```tsx
import { getLegalPages } from "~/app/(app)/(content)/_lib/source";

export function generateStaticParams() {
  return getLegalPages().map((page) => ({ slug: page.slugs[0] }));
}
```

#### 3. Docs OG Handler

**File** (new): `apps/www/src/app/(app)/(content)/docs/(general)/[[...slug]]/opengraph-image.tsx`

```tsx
import { DocsLayout } from "@repo/og";
import { OG_HEIGHT, OG_WIDTH } from "@repo/og/brand";
import { ImageResponse } from "next/og";
import { getPage, getPages } from "~/app/(app)/(content)/_lib/source";
import { loadOGFonts } from "~/lib/og-fonts";

export const runtime = "nodejs";
export const alt = "Lightfast Documentation";
export const size = { width: OG_WIDTH, height: OG_HEIGHT };
export const contentType = "image/png";

export default async function Image({
  params,
}: {
  params: Promise<{ slug?: string[] }>;
}) {
  const { slug } = await params;
  const fonts = await loadOGFonts();

  if (!slug || slug.length === 0) {
    return new ImageResponse(
      <DocsLayout title="Documentation" />,
      { ...size, fonts }
    );
  }

  const page = getPage(slug);

  if (!page) {
    return new ImageResponse(<div>Not Found</div>, { ...size });
  }

  const title = page.data.title ?? "Documentation";

  return new ImageResponse(
    <DocsLayout
      breadcrumb={slug.map((s) =>
        s.split("-").map((w) => (w[0]?.toUpperCase() ?? "") + w.slice(1)).join(" ")
      )}
      title={title}
    />,
    { ...size, fonts }
  );
}

export function generateStaticParams() {
  return getPages().map((page) => ({ slug: page.slugs }));
}
```

#### 4. API Reference OG Handler

**File** (new): `apps/www/src/app/(app)/(content)/docs/(api)/api-reference/[[...slug]]/opengraph-image.tsx`

```tsx
import { DocsLayout } from "@repo/og";
import { OG_HEIGHT, OG_WIDTH } from "@repo/og/brand";
import { ImageResponse } from "next/og";
import { getApiPage, getApiPages } from "~/app/(app)/(content)/_lib/source";
import { loadOGFonts } from "~/lib/og-fonts";

export const runtime = "nodejs";
export const alt = "Lightfast API Reference";
export const size = { width: OG_WIDTH, height: OG_HEIGHT };
export const contentType = "image/png";

export default async function Image({
  params,
}: {
  params: Promise<{ slug?: string[] }>;
}) {
  const { slug } = await params;
  const fonts = await loadOGFonts();

  if (!slug || slug.length === 0) {
    return new ImageResponse(
      <DocsLayout section="API Reference" title="API Reference" />,
      { ...size, fonts }
    );
  }

  const page = getApiPage(slug);

  if (!page) {
    return new ImageResponse(<div>Not Found</div>, { ...size });
  }

  const title = page.data.title ?? "API Reference";

  return new ImageResponse(
    <DocsLayout
      section="API Reference"
      title={title}
    />,
    { ...size, fonts }
  );
}

export function generateStaticParams() {
  return getApiPages().map((page) => ({ slug: page.slugs }));
}
```

### Success Criteria

#### Automated Verification

- [ ] `pnpm typecheck` passes — new `featuredImage` field compiles, new files have no type errors
- [ ] `pnpm build:www` succeeds — OG route handlers generate images at build time
- [ ] `pnpm check` passes — lint clean

#### Manual Verification

- [ ] Visit `/legal/privacy/opengraph-image` — renders a "Legal" category OG image with title
- [ ] Visit `/docs/get-started/overview/opengraph-image` — renders a Docs OG image with breadcrumb
- [ ] Visit `/docs/api-reference/overview/opengraph-image` — renders an API Reference OG image
- [ ] Existing blog/changelog OG images still work (no regression)

**Implementation Note**: After completing this phase and all automated verification passes, pause here for manual confirmation from the human that the manual testing was successful before proceeding to the next phase.

---

## Phase 2: Migrate Consumers

### Overview

Swap every consumer of `ogImage` to use either `featuredImage` (for hero images) or the programmatic OG URL (for metadata/feeds/JSON-LD). After this phase, `ogImage` is still in the schema but no code reads it.

### Changes Required

#### 1. SEO Bundle: Remove `openGraph.images` and `twitter.images`

**File**: `apps/www/src/lib/seo-bundle.ts`

In `buildArticleMetadata` (lines 37-86), remove the `images` property from both `openGraph` and `twitter`:

```ts
// Before (lines 69-71):
images: [
  { url: data.ogImage, width: 1200, height: 630, alt: data.ogTitle },
],

// After: remove entirely — colocated opengraph-image.tsx provides this
```

```ts
// Before (line 80):
images: [data.ogImage],

// After: remove entirely
```

Same change in `emitLegalSeo` (lines 137-180):
- Remove `images` from `openGraph` (lines 165-167)
- Remove `images` from `twitter` (line 175)

#### 2. JSON-LD Builders: Use Programmatic OG URL

**File**: `apps/www/src/lib/builders/blog.ts`

Change `buildBlogPostEntity` to accept `url` and derive the OG image URL:

```ts
// Before (function signature, line 20):
function buildBlogPostEntity(
  data: BlogPostData
): Omit<BlogPosting, "@id" | "url"> {

// After:
function buildBlogPostEntity(
  data: BlogPostData,
  url: BlogPostUrl
): Omit<BlogPosting, "@id" | "url"> {
```

```ts
// Before (lines 36-41):
image: {
  "@type": "ImageObject" as const,
  url: data.ogImage,
  width: "1200",
  height: "630",
},

// After:
image: {
  "@type": "ImageObject" as const,
  url: `${url}/opengraph-image`,
  width: "1200",
  height: "630",
},
```

Update the call site at line 54:
```ts
// Before:
const entity = buildBlogPostEntity(data);

// After:
const entity = buildBlogPostEntity(data, url);
```

**File**: `apps/www/src/lib/builders/changelog.ts`

Same pattern — add `url: ChangelogUrl` parameter to `buildChangelogEntryEntity` and replace `data.ogImage` with `${url}/opengraph-image`.

#### 3. Blog Page: Use `featuredImage` for Hero

**File**: `apps/www/src/app/(app)/(marketing)/(content)/blog/[slug]/page.tsx`

```ts
// Before (line 50):
    ogImage,

// After:
    featuredImage,
```

```tsx
